<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURA PALMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Basketball 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont to Change Coaches -- Frank Foggiano was relieved of his duties as 
Grossmont High's boys' and girls' basketball coach, it was announced. 
</P>
<P>
"It was simply that the basketball program wasn't going in the direction that 
we thought it should," Grossmont Athletic Director Judd Hulbert said. "It's not 
any one particular thing." 
</P>
<P>
Last season the boys' team finished 6-17 and third in the Grossmont 2-A League 
at 2-4. The girls were 6-17 and 0-6. Foggiano coached the boys' team for 10 
years and the girls' team for six. 
</P>
<P>
Hulbert said Foggiano will continue teaching at the school. LAURA PALMER 
</P>
