<P>
END OF MARTIAL LAW TERMED SUPERFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Dalai Lama said that China's lifting of martial law in his homeland was a 
"public relations exercise." 
</P>
<P>
He called for a fundamental change in the way Chinese leaders view Tibet. 
Martial law was imposed in the capital of Lhasa a year ago after anti-Chinese 
rioting left as many as 30 dead. The exiled Dalai Lama has called for an 
autonomous Tibet where Beijing would still control defense and foreign 
relations. 
</P>
