<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Warner Bros. to Film 'Phantom:' Warner Bros. will make "The Phantom of the 
Opera," Andrew Lloyd Webber's musical hit about the lovestruck murderer who 
terrorized the Paris Opera House. 
</P>
<P>
Filming is expected to begin late this year, with a scheduled Thanksgiving 1991 
release. Michael Crawford, who wound up a 3 1/2-year stage stint as the Phantom 
on Sunday at Los Angeles' Ahmanson Theatre, will re-create his role in the 
film. Starring as Christine, the object of the Phantom's desires, will be Sarah 
Brightman, who is Lloyd Webber's wife. The film will be directed by Joel 
Schumacher, who directed "Cousins" and "The Lost Boys." GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
