<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: RESTAURANT MANAGER SHOT TO DEATH BY ROBBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The manager of a restaurant in Playa del Rey was shot to death when one of two 
robbers opened fire for no apparent reason, Los Angeles police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Detective Chuck Worthen of the LAPD's Pacific Division station said the robbers 
entered the Bob's Big Boy cafe in the 8000 block of Manchester Boulevard about 
11 p.m. Monday, an hour after closing time. The pair produced guns, walked up 
to the manager, 29-year-old Albert Brodeur Jr. of Redondo Beach, and demanded 
money, Worthen said. 
</P>
<P>
Before Brodeur could respond, one of the men shot him several times, police 
said. Both men ran from the restaurant. It was not immediately determined 
whether any money was taken. 
</P>
</TEXT>
