Chevron to Sell Some Assets: Chevron U.S.A. Inc. said it has agreed to sell 
certain Gulf of Mexico oil reserves for about $150 million to a New 
Orleans-based partnership. Chevron U.S.A., the domestic oil and gas subsidiary 
of Chevron Corp., said it will sell its Main Pass 299 shallow oil reserves, 
