<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
UFW FOUNDER ASKS UCI TO JOIN BOYCOTT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
United Farm Workers founder Cesar Chavez received a standing ovation from more 
than 430 people who packed a UC Irvine auditorium Tuesday to hear him ask for 
support of the 4-year-old boycott of table grapes. The grapes boycott -- the 
third organized by UFW since it was founded 28 years ago -- is aimed at forcing 
growers to stop using pesticides, which Chavez and other union members blame 
for an alarming increase of cancer among farm workers in the Central Valley. 
</P>
<P>
The East Los Angeles-based roots-rock band Los Lobos made a surprise appearance 
to show its support for the boycott and for Chavez. 
</P>
<P>
Chavez is encouraging students at 11 Southern California campuses this week to 
fast for one day in observance of his cause. 
</P>
</TEXT>
