NEWSWIRE: TAPES SOUGHT IN BLACKMAIL TRIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government will subpoena tape recordings given to the New York Daily News 
by a gambler accused of trying to blackmail New York Yankee owner George 
Steinbrenner, a prosecutor said. 
</P>
<P>
During a brief status conference in Tampa, Fla., the trial of Howie Spira, 30, 
of the Bronx in New York City was tentatively scheduled for July. U.S. District 
Judge William Castagna set no specific date. 
</P>
<P>
An eight-count indictment charges Spira, who was not at the hearing, with using 
letters and telephone calls to extort and threaten Steinbrenner and outfielder 
Dave Winfield. 
</P>
