SOVIETS AGAIN WIN HOCKEY TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BERN, Switzerland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Soviet Union successfully defended its title at the World Hockey 
Championships today with a 5-0 rout of Czechoslovakia. 
</P>
<P>
Valeri Kamenski's two goals led the scoring. 
</P>
<P>
It was the 22nd gold medal for the Soviets since they first competed in the 
championships in 1954, and their third in five years. 
</P>
<P>
The Soviets finished the medal round with a 3-0 record after earlier victories 
over Sweden and Canada. Czechoslovakia was 1-1-1. 
</P>
<P>
The Soviets notched three goals in just over five minutes of the third period. 
</P>
