<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO SHORTAGE OF ROOTERS FOR SUMMER SQUALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LOUISVILLE, Ky. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Should Summer Squall win the Kentucky Derby Saturday, they'll have to draw 
straws to see who gets into the winner's circle. 
</P>
<P>
There is a 20-person limit in the winner's circle. 
</P>
<P>
The colt has 28 owners who are members of Dogwood Stable's Classic partnership 
that purchased yearling colts by five leading sires -- Storm Bird, Nijinsky II, 
Nureyev, Alydar and Danzig. 
</P>
<P>
Cot Campbell, president of Dogwood Stable, said not all the partners would 
attend the Derby, but there would be a group of 25, including spouses. 
</P>
<P>
The 28 people purchased 40 shares in the partnerships at $55,900 a share. 
</P>
<P>
Holding more than one share are Ray Roncari, Mrs. John Ben Ali Haggin and Paul 
Oreffice. Oreffice is board chairman of Dow Chemical Co. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
